</disciplines><abstract>&lt;p&gt;In 2016, the citizens of Knoxville, Tennessee, joined in a community reading program called the Big Read. Knoxvillians read Ernest Gaines&#39;s book &lt;em&gt;A Lesson Before Dying&lt;/em&gt;, and community groups hosted a series of lectures, book discussions, film screenings, and dramatic performances that immersed the community in a five-week conversation on racism.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This book of essays is the University of Tennessee Libraries&#39; contribution to Knoxville&#39;s Big Read. The Libraries put out a community-wide call for written responses to &lt;em&gt;A Lesson Before Dying&lt;/em&gt; and was richly rewarded with the thoughtful and heartfelt commentaries gathered here.&lt;/p&gt;</abstract>
